com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.base

Interface IScriptTask


  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
 @ThreadSafe
public interface IScriptTask
    IScriptTask represents a created script task from the client side script. The script task can be called, to execute the client code. See call(IServiceContext, Object...) method to execute the script task.

    The script task has a defined IScriptTaskType, which defines where the task is executable and what argument are passed to the task during execution. See IScriptTaskType for details.

    The script task is created hold by an IScript, see IScript for more details.

    Load behavior
    The script task instance will not change, when a script is reloaded due to changes. So the user code, can hold a reference to the IScriptTask when the script is changed.

    All method parameters and return values must be non-null unless documented otherwise.

    • Method Detail

      • call

        @PublishedMethod
IScriptTaskExecutionResult call(IServiceContext serviceContext,
                                                  java.lang.Object... args)
        Calls the task code to execute it.

        The signature of this method is defined by the IScriptTaskType, see getTaskType(). So the args Object[] must contain instance of the types defined in the IScriptTaskType of this IScriptTask, otherwise the script is not callable.

        Parameters:
        serviceContext - the serviceContext to call the task in. If the task is a project task it must be a ProjectContext, otherwise it must be an ApplicationContext.
        args - the args which are passed the the IScriptTask.
        Returns:
        the return object from the script.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException -
        • if the the execution of the task has failed.
        See Also:
        IScriptTaskType, IScriptTaskType.IScriptTaskTypeSignature, IScriptTaskExecutionResult
